The fishmongers was owned by a man called Arthur Bryan. After matches, Bryan would feed the club's players as well as those of the visiting side haddock and chips. With a South London accent, it would sound like addick and chips. /4

The club is known as the Addicks. One might think that it's slang for Athletic but it's not. According to the club's history on their website, it harkens back to the time when the club was formed by local teenagers on East Street, South London where a fishmongers was located. /3
